FRONTEND ENV — SoumyaOps
=========================
Copy the lines below into a file named: frontend/.env
(Vite reads .env files automatically)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PASTE THIS INTO: frontend/.env
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
VITE_APP_NAME=SoumyaOps
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_ENABLE_WEBSOCKET=true
VITE_ENABLE_STREAMING=true


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
WHAT EACH VARIABLE DOES — LINE BY LINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
  → The URL of your backend Express server.
  → In LOCAL development: http://localhost:4000
    Vite's proxy (vite.config.js) forwards /api → this URL automatically.
    So in your browser you never see localhost:4000 directly.
  → In PRODUCTION (Vercel deploy): https://your-app.railway.app
    Change this in the Vercel dashboard under Environment Variables.

VITE_APP_NAME=SoumyaOps
  → Used in browser tab title and any <title> tags.
  → Change to your team's name if you fork this.

VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
  → Shown in About pages or debug info.
  → Not critical, can leave as-is.

VITE_ENABLE_WEBSOCKET=true
  → true  = WebSocket connects to backend for real-time job progress.
             You see live deployment progress bars without refreshing.
  → false = Disable if your hosting doesn't support persistent connections.
             Pages will still work but won't show live progress.

VITE_ENABLE_STREAMING=true
  → true  = RAG chat uses SSE streaming (/api/rag/query/stream).
             Words appear one by one as Claude generates them.
  → false = Uses the blocking endpoint (/api/rag/query).
             Full response appears all at once after a delay.


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
NOTE ABOUT VITE_ PREFIX
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

IMPORTANT: Every variable the frontend uses MUST start with VITE_
Vite strips all other variables for security.
In your code you read them like this:
  const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;

NEVER put secrets (API keys, passwords) in the frontend .env.
Frontend code is visible to anyone who opens browser DevTools.
All secrets live ONLY in the backend .env (see soumyac.txt).


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT — you only need ONE change:
  Leave VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
  Everything else works with default values.

FOR PRODUCTION (Vercel):
  VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app
  Set this in: Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━